38%200%200140%200c0-1%2037-2%2038%200%200%201%201%201%201-1%201-1%202-2%206-2%205%200%205-1%205-3s0-2%2014-2h14v7h19l20%201h1l18-1%2020%201c1%201%201-1%201-8v-9h-28l13%201h14v6h-19l-13-1%205-1v-2l-2-2-1%202v1l-1-2c1-1%200-1-4-1l-4%201%201%201%201%201c0%202%200%202-1%201h-1a968%20968%200%2000-70%206c0%202%200%202-1%200l-4-3-81-1H80v-16h42c50-1%2050-1%2047-5-1-1-1-1-2%201h-2c0-1-1-2-3-2l15-1h19v4c0%203%200%203%201-2l1-9v-3h-20l-14-1c5%200%205-1%205-3s0-2%2015-2l15-1h-18l-15%201c2%200%202%201%201%202h-2l-3-2h-2l-1-1-1%203v4l-39%201H80v-17h236v-7h39v-4l1-5H237v8h-39v-8h-40c-31%200-35%201-20%201l20%201v6h-19c-18%200-24%200-14-1%204-1%205-1%205-3s-3-3-3%200h-1c0-2-5-3-6-1v3c-1%202-2%202-21%202H80v-32h138a7887%207887%200%200078-1h-19v-4l-1-4v8h-78v-4l-1-4v8h-38v-4l-1-4v8h-39v-4l-1-4v8H80v-8l-1-8v8m158%2066v8l4-1h3a1077%201077%200%200095%201h14v-7l1%204%201%204v-10h-20a1935%201935%200%2001-87-2v-3l-2%201c-2%202-2%202-2%200l-3-2h-2l-1-1-1%208\\'%20fill=\\'%23d3d3d3\\'%20fill-rule=\\'evenodd\\'/%3e%3c/svg%3e'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/e6be1b56e5f759dcdd51a8198b33a678/ba381/speedtest-calendar.webp 200w,\n/static/e6be1b56e5f759dcdd51a8198b33a678/7f61c/speedtest-calendar.webp 400w,\n/static/e6be1b56e5f759dcdd51a8198b33a678/d00b9/speedtest-calendar.webp 800w,\n/static/e6be1b56e5f759dcdd51a8198b33a678/92f8c/speedtest-calendar.webp 1200w,\n/static/e6be1b56e5f759dcdd51a8198b33a678/fad48/speedtest-calendar.webp 1600w,\n/static/e6be1b56e5f759dcdd51a8198b33a678/8df42/speedtest-calendar.webp 2048w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/e6be1b56e5f759dcdd51a8198b33a678/772e8/speedtest-calendar.png 200w,\n/static/e6be1b56e5f759dcdd51a8198b33a678/e17e5/speedtest-calendar.png 400w,\n/static/e6be1b56e5f759dcdd51a8198b33a678/5a190/speedtest-calendar.png 800w,\n/static/e6be1b56e5f759dcdd51a8198b33a678/c1b63/speedtest-calendar.png 1200w,\n/static/e6be1b56e5f759dcdd51a8198b33a678/29007/speedtest-calendar.png 1600w,\n/static/e6be1b56e5f759dcdd51a8198b33a678/a878e/speedtest-calendar.png 2048w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/e6be1b56e5f759dcdd51a8198b33a678/5a190/speedtest-calendar.png\"\n          alt=\"Speedtest calendar\"\n          title=\"Speedtest calendar\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>A quick monitoring project.</p>\n<p>As anyone from the UK will know, our internet speeds <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://www.speedtest.net/global-index\" title=\"aren't quite up to par with the rest of the developed world\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">aren't quite up to par with the rest of the developed world</a>.</p>\n<p>Whilst at university, my internet was being provided by BT, and the fastest we could supposedly get was 35mb download speeds.\nHowever, we were having constant dropouts and nothing was being done about it.\nSo, I though I would try to monitor the internet a bit closer, I had a spare RPI hanging around not really doing much besides a minecraft server, and thought it would be an interesting experiment.</p>\n<p>So, I set up an <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://ifttt.com/\" title=\"IFTTT\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">IFTTT</a> webhook, and a cronjob on the RPI to automatically update a Google Sheets document with the latest speedtest results.</p>\n<p>Inspiration thanks to <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://makezine.com/projects/send-ticket-isp-when-your-internet-drops/\" title=\"this project\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">this project</a>, and I've had a lot of fun experimenting with the data retrieved.</p>\n<p>As it turns out, we have NEVER achieved our advertised internet speed, and dropped out a number of times in the few months I have run this (although as it only runs every half hour, I'm pretty sure we have dropped out more frequently than this).</p>\n<p>Other interesting insights from this data include seeing how the <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-51947447\" title=\"Coronavirus internet surge\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">Coronavirus internet surge</a> did in fact slow down our internet as everyone moved to remote work.</p>","excerpt":"A quick monitoring project. As anyone from the UK will know, our internet speeds . Whilst at university, my internet was being provided by BT, and the fastest we could supposedly get was 35mb download…","frontmatter":{"title":"⚡️ Automated speedtest internet monitoring","date":"January, 2020","tech":["IFTTT","Google Sheets"],"link":"https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/14zlZ_uNWS6K2Gvyf4sXMoyiGnk4NEURDnzkeZhzdHOg/edit?usp=sharing","source":null,"previewImage":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/static/e6be1b56e5f759dcdd51a8198b33a678/f3583/speedtest-calendar.png","height":894,"width":1200}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/projects/speedtest/"}}}